organizer joel ferguson said friday he's confident jackson will be enough of a newsmaker that he can count on being on television without having to buy commercial time
jackson will spend the three days before michigan's march 26 democratic caucuses barnstorming the state, and has a full schedule of appearances before that, beginning with a commencement address today at michigan state university
after the address, jackson is scheduled to meet with supporters, labor leaders and gov. james blanchard _ activities that will be parallelled by rival michael dukakis, who plans today to tour a lansing machine tool plant before meeting with labor and the democratic governor
blanchard met thursday with rep. richard gephardt of missouri, another democratic contender
new york gov. mario cuomo thinks independent counsel lawrence walsh could do democrats a favor by delaying the release of any information that might link vice president george bush to the iran-contra affair
the worst thing that could happen now is to have some kind of exposure of irangate that knocks bush out and makes room for (bob) dole,'' cuomo said friday of bush's recent success in republican super tuesday primaries
cuomo has joked in the past that the best republican ticket, from a democratic standpoint, would be ``bush and bush.'' the governor has said dole would be harder for the democrats to beat
if there's going to be some revelation, let it come after it's too late to change bush,'' cuomo said of walsh's investigation
