why is k mart america's favorite store?'' asked valentin v. kozitzyn, here for a soviet cultural exhibit
and another thing: why do americans have to drink different kinds of beer at different times of the day, he asked
kozitsyn had seen the commercial asserting ``the night belongs to michelob.''
he said the average soviet probably knows more about american culture than soviet culture, and that part of solving that shortcoming lies in modern p.r. techniques
there is much we need to teach our own people, and much to learn about accomplishing that,'' kozitsyn said
