we urge illinois republicans to give enthusiastic validation to the bush candidacy,'' the sun-times editorial board said in a statement issued friday
the editors cited bush's past experience as a congressman, cia director, united nations ambassador, national party chairman as well as his current position as vice president
rarely has a presidential candidate offered the variety and texture of public experience that mr. bush represents,'' the editorial board said
mr. bush has more inside knowledge of the workings of more aspects of government than all but a few candidates in two centuries,'' the newspaper's editors said
we have supreme confidence in mr. bush's understanding of international affairs and his capability for stewardship in guiding the united states through the mine fields of world politics,'' the editors said
