ray murray, 34, of atlanta, identified as a special agent for the dea, was charged with possession of marijuana after police, who were watching an area of known drug transactions, saw a man purchase two packets of a substance shortly before 1 p.m., police said
murray, who was arrested about a block away, was one of 30 people arrested saturday afternoon on narcotics distribution or possession charges, police said. he was scheduled for arraignment monday
prince edward, the youngest son of queen elizabeth ii, plans to marry the 22-year-old daughter of a belgian baroness, a weekly newspaper reported sunday
the people, a london tabloid, said the 24-year-old prince has proposed to georgia may, whose mother catherine was born a baroness in belgium's van den branden de reeth family
edward would have to give up his rights as fifth in line to the british throne if he married miss may, a roman catholic, the newspaper said
britain's 1701 act of settlement rules that only protestants may become british monarchs
the newspaper said the prince is awaiting the queen's permission to be formally engaged
it quoted miss may's former boyfriend, new zealand yachtsman ed danby, as saying she told him of the engagement plan in a telephone call last week
